<br>
She appeared in the usual attire, looking the same as always. She wasn't much for big entrances or using her God like powers or anything like that. So instead of just poofing in like most people did, she pushed open the door and came in quietly. She saw anybody who was there -- and stopped short on Belle. And this is where the pride would come in. Alexa stood quietly by herself, refusing to talk to anyone unless spoken to.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daughterofshylock>Daughter of Shylock</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.picturesof.net/_wallpaper/rose_Dsc08151_WP.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 195<br> <font color=#993300>(2/16/03 11:06:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=275.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.picturesof.net/_wallpaper/rose_Dsc08151_WP.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Alexas Entrance</span><hr size=1> Nikita smiled over to Alysia as she looked at the new baby and then to Aliya, Alexa and Belle. Nikita grinned lightly and looked to her niece.<br>
