<br>
 Angel finally entered behind Wulf. For once, the young girl looked shy, and innocent. Blue pools fell upon the floor, as she slid against Wulf's side. All of these people were new, all of this was an experience she didn't feel at all prepared for.<br>
<br>
 Her hand slipped inside Wulf's, and she squeezed it gently for a reassurance, as she finally brought her eyes up to him.<br>
<br>
 At that moment, she wanted to break into tears. She had lost her brother, and now here she was at a family reunion, longing for what family she had left.. and it wasn't there anymore.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>-Dawnithinia-</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
 Dawn stayed silent, settling into her corner of the tavern. Large crowds were common amongst the Loire's, and amongst the amazons, and the solitary assassin had gotten well use to the appearences of many. <br>
<br>
 But as they all grew in numbers, Dawn grew into the darkness. Her arms wrapped delicately around her now, sleeping Andra. One never knew when someone would attack, and Dawn surely wasn't willing to risk her child to find out when.<br>
<br>
 For once the assassin felt dependent, upon her child, for her child depended on its mother's strong will and ability to protect her, and Dawn depended on Ares support, to keep watch, and to help her through. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>-Lilla Ann-</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
 Lilla sighed, settling at a table with her hand once more full of grapes, methodically popping one into her mouth every once and awhile. Lilla had become a people watcher in her years alone, and a Loire family reunion seemed as though it was the perfect place to watch. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=melodyloire@amazonsunite>Melody Loire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#993300>(2/21/03 4:24:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=275.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Twins..?</span><hr size=1> She returned the hug and in the midst of it, gazed over her mother's shoulder at the growing crowd. Interesting bunch, it seemed. But, after the introductions, after all the hugging and, 'Oh, it's been ages since I've seen you!' how interesting would they seem and become? She drew away from Aliya, though only to be turned toward Alexa, whom she blinked and stared at. Aliya talked about her a lot. And, apparently, for good reason.<br>
<br>
With a bit of nervous flourish, she bowed shallowly at the hip and offered another wan smile. &quot;Um, hello, Aunt Alexa.&quot;<br>
